{"id":"259510203_Cycle-aware_minimization_of_acyclic_deterministic_finite-state_automata","abstract":"In this paper a linear-time algorithm for the minimization of acyclic deterministic finite-state automata is presented. The algorithm runs significantly faster than previous algorithms for the same task. This is shown by a comparison of the running times of both algorithms. Additionally, a variation of the new algorithm is presented which handles cyclic automata as input. The new cycle-aware algorithm minimizes acyclic automata in the desired way. In case of cyclic input, the algorithm minimizes all acyclic suffixes of the input automaton.","authors":["Johannes Bubenzer"],"meta":["January 2014Discrete Applied Mathematics 163:238â€“246","DOI:10.1016/j.dam.2013.08.003"],"references":["228382656_Taxonomies_and_toolkits_of_regular_language_algorithms","220355507_Incremental_Construction_of_Minimal_Acyclic_Finite-State_Automata","2781981_A_Taxonomy_of_Finite_Automata_Construction_Algorithms","2504689_A_Taxonomy_of_Algorithms_for_Constructing_Minimal_Acyclic_Deterministic_Finite_Automata","288307465_Minimization_of_acyclic_DFAs","242552512_Finite_Automata_and_Representation_of_Events","239041872_Canonical_regular_expressions_and_minimal_state_graphs_for_definite_events","235208212_An_N_Log_N_Algorithm_for_Minimizing_States_in_a_Finite_Automaton","230876336_Gedanken-Experiments_on_Sequential_Machines","229124581_Linear_Automaton_Transformations","225862272_fsm2_-_A_Scripting_Language_Interpreter_for_Manipulating_Weighted_Finite-State_Automata","223689543_Re-describing_an_algorithm_by_Hopcroft","223122265_Minimisation_of_acyclic_deterministic_automata_in_linear_time","222307580_The_Synthesis_of_Sequential_Switching_Circuits","221568184_Comparison_of_Construction_Algorithms_for_Minimal_Acyclic_Deterministic_Finite-State_Automata_from_Sets_of_Strings","220198267_Describing_an_Algorithm_by_Hopcroft"]}